A. The Computing System

1. Fundamentals of thermodynamic computing

We begin by reviewing thermodynamic computing, which is a relatively young field, and hence the theoretical concepts are still being worked out. We focus here on the paradigm of CV thermodynamic computing from Refs. [13, 15, 16], which is based on the stochastic dynamics of a physical system acted on by a combination of conservative, dissipative, and fluctuating forces. These dynamics can be modeled by the underdamped Langevin (UDL) stochastic differential equations (SDEs)

dx = M −1p dt

