E. Uncertainty quantification for neural networks
Neural networks enable classification of high-dimensional data and largely provide the foundation for modern machine learning. However, a key shortcoming is the “overconfidence” of the predictions made by neural networks. This phenomenon corresponds to out-of-distribution data being classified with high certainty as belonging to one of the learned classes. Uncertainty quantification (UQ) provides means to tackle the overconfidence issue, and is crucial for making AI more reliable.
Here we focus on a state-of-the-art method for UQ in neural network classification called spectralnormalized neural Gaussian processes (SNGP) [27]. SNGP involves replacing the output layer of a deep

