The current design of the PCB has an unfortunate property that makes the unit cells have different properties when they should be identical. For example, when setting up the device to have the identity covariance matrix, the covariance matrix of the samples does not have a uniform diagonal as would be expected. Specifically, the variances are monotonically increasing with the cell number; cell 0 has a smaller variance than cell 7 even when both cells have the same capacitance.
